  <eligibility>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

        (i) symptoms [New York Heart Association (NYHA) class II or III] and signs typical of heart
        failure

        (ii) left ventricular (LV) ejection fraction (LVEF) &gt;50% and LV end-diastolic volume index
        &lt;97 mL/m2

        (iii) findings of left atrial (LA) dilatation (LA volume index &gt;40mL/m2), LV hypertrophy
        and/or LV diastolic dysfunction [ie, mitral E/A ratio &lt;1 or &gt;2, mitral E/e' ratio &gt;15 or
        8-15, (A pulmonary - A mitral) duration difference &gt;30 ms etc)

        (iv) no alterations in medical therapy during the previous 4 weeks

        (v) no myocardial infarction within 3 months prior to enrollment

        Exclusion Criteria:

        recent (â‰¤4 weeks) heart failure decompensation

          -  acute coronary syndrome

          -  chronic inflammatory diseases and malignancies
      </textblock>
